Definition.WordDefinition:
Highness \High"ness\, n. [AS. he['a]hnes.] 1. The state of being high; elevation; loftiness. [1913 Webster]
2. A title of honor given to kings, princes, or other persons of rank; as, His Royal Highness. --Shak. [1913 Webster]
Highness n 1: (Your Highness or His Highness of Her Highness) title used to address a royal person 2: the condition of being high or lofty [syn: {loftiness}] [ant: {lowness}]
